In this section, some convenient solutions on safe domestic wastewater management were tested with actual data of five cities in Southeast Asian countries (Buon Ma thuota, Vietnam; Yogyakarta, Indonesia, Hadyai, Patong and Tharae, Thailand) using the four wastewater management indicators which were: collection performance, treatment performance, cost-benefit ratio, and social content. These five cities were selected because they have similar size and domestic wastewater management conditions which are non-sewered sanitation with decentralized treatment systems (CWWA 2009; Bill and Melin da Gates Foundation 2012). Details of the domestic wastewater management data of these five cities, presented in Table 2
                        , were used in plotting a domestic wastewater management effectiveness chart (Fig. 6
                        ) to accomplish SDG6 targets. In this research, a city is considered to have effective domestic wastewater management if all the four wastewater management indicators were equal to or greater than the ‘satisfactory’ level.
